  "text": "We are able to cheaply and easily collect labels for all images by first sparsely reconstructing each scene using COLMAP [CITATION_1] , and then densely reconstructing the scene using CMVS [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Following reconstruction, we label each object in the dense 3D point cloud and project the labeled point cloud to a bounding box in each image. Using depth data from the Kinect, we are able to automatically adjust the bounding boxes projected from the point cloud to account for occlusion. Moreover, we are also able to get consistent object pose information for every image in the scene by labeling just a single image per object and using the camera positions from the reconstruction to discern the pose of the object in every image. Table 6 . Results on the Household Dataset. Evaluation on the household data, results are shown for our model trained on (P3D), then fine-tuned on the household data (P3D+finetune), and for our model trained only on the household data (scratch). We include the results of our P3D model on the P3D+ dataset in order to roughly compare the difficulty of the datasets for these categories.",
